    <abstract id="aspace_c3daa1f354a16dc65af47fc363b5c009">Handbills and serials published by Glad Day Press, including material concerning the Vietnam War, the Black Liberation Movement, Students for a Democratic Society (SDS); and the Cornell University Carpenter Hall takeover, May 1972. Serials include Caw! and New Left Notes (both published by the SDS), Mobilizer, Cornell-Ithaca Mobilizer, The First Issue, Workers Bulletin, Watu (published by The Black Literary Society of Cornell University), Dateline: Ithaca, New Patriot, Volunteers, Tiohero, and Notes from a Green Piano. Also, photographs, newsletters, publications, drafts of articles and speeches, and a calendar.</abstract>
